          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Amends the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 to establish a 10-year statute of limitations governing an action or proceeding by the Securities and Exchange Commission for a civil monetary penalty. </p> <p>Tolls this statute of limitations any time an alleged violator is either absent from the United States or has no reasonably ascertainable place of abode or work within it. </p>]]></text>
        </item>
